4. Vehicles**

ğŸš† Trains (Two directions)

* **Train 1** moves left
* **Train 2** moves right
* Each train has:

  * Locomotive
  * Chimney
  * Windows
  * Wheels (circular)
  * Passenger cars
* Speed controlled via keyboard

---
 ğŸš— Cars

* Two cars moving in opposite directions
* Features:

  * Body
  * Roof
  * Windows
  * Wheels
* Speed adjustable via keyboard

---

â›µ Boats

* Two boats moving across river
* Reset position after leaving screen

---

ğŸˆ Hot Air Balloon

* Moves automatically
* Can be **dragged using mouse**
* Bounded within screen limits

---

5. Animation System (`updateScene`)

Uses **GLUT timer**:

```cpp
glutTimerFunc(50, updateScene, 0);
```

Handles:

* Train movement
* Car movement
* Cloud drift
* Boat movement
* Balloon auto-movement (if not dragged)
* Pause/Resume support

---

 6. Interaction

 âŒ¨ Keyboard Controls

| Key     | Action                  |
| ------- | ----------------------- |
| `Y / N` | Day / Night mode        |
| `Q / A` | Train-1 speed up / down |
| `W / S` | Train-2 speed up / down |
| `E / D` | Car-1 speed up / down   |
| `R / F` | Car-2 speed up / down   |
| `SPACE` | Pause / Resume          |
| `X`     | Reset all speeds        |

---

 ğŸ–± Mouse Controls

* **Click & drag** hot air balloon
* Cursor changes when hovering balloon
* Screen-to-world coordinate conversion used

---

7. Rendering (`drawScene`)

* Clears screen
* Sets background color based on time
* Draws objects in correct **layer order**
* Ensures smooth animation

---

8. Key Programming Concepts Used

* OpenGL **immediate mode**
* **2D transformations**
* **Timer-based animation**
* **Keyboard & mouse handling**
* **Trigonometric animation (sin wave)**
* **Bounding & reset logic**
* Modular function design









